post_text: Congratulations Anthony! Way to represent Harrison High School.
shared_text:
Harrison High School Debate Team
February 10, 2019 at 12:29 AM ·

Congratulations to Harrison High School Debate Team sophomore Anthony Kang '21 on placing 2nd at the Bronx High School of Science's Winter Local tournament this weekend!

Anthony, Harrison's only entry at the tournament, was undefeated in the JV division, and was 2nd speaker. This season, he has reached varsity elimination rounds at several bid tournaments, including Princeton, Ridge, Newark, and Columbia, in addition to placing at several local tournaments. Anthony will next represent Harrison at Harvard's national tournament next weekend. We look forward to seeing his continued success there and far into the future!
text:
Congratulations Anthony! Way to represent Harrison High School.

Harrison High School Debate Team
February 10, 2019 at 12:29 AM ·

Congratulations to Harrison High School Debate Team sophomore Anthony Kang '21 on placing 2nd at the Bronx High School of Science's Winter Local tournament this weekend!

Anthony, Harrison's only entry at the tournament, was undefeated in the JV division, and was 2nd speaker. This season, he has reached varsity elimination rounds at several bid tournaments, including Princeton, Ridge, Newark, and Columbia, in addition to placing at several local tournaments. Anthony will next represent Harrison at Harvard's national tournament next weekend. We look forward to seeing his continued success there and far into the future!

post_text: Congrats to the Harrison High School Debate team who captured 3 of the top 5 places in the novice division at the Bronx Science Tournament.
shared_text:
Harrison High School Debate Team
November 17, 2018 at 11:35 PM ·

Congratulations to the Harrison High School Debate Team novices on a great showing at this weekend's Bronx Science Fall Local tournament at the Bronx High School of Science! All six of our students had winning records and received awards!

Ali Ahmad '22 placed 2nd, Milly Wong '22 placed 3rd, Gabe Voskoff '22 placed 4th, Macarena Hesse '22 placed 9th, Arun Sood '22 placed 12th, and Lizzie Murno '22 placed 16th! Ali, Milly, Gabe, and Macarena were all undefeated!

Special thanks to Darin Iraj '20 for judging, and to Dana Rubin for chaperoning and judging!

The novices will next compete alongside the varsity at Princeton University's tournament the weekend after next.

Congrats to all!

(Left to right: Arun Sood '22, Gabe Voskoff '22, Milly Wong '22, judge Darin Iraj '20, Lizzie Murno '22, Macarena Hesse '22, Ali Ahmad '22)

post_text: Congratulations to Giovanni and Rebecca!!!
shared_text:
Harrison High School Debate Team is at German International School New York.
October 28, 2018 at 6:14 PM · White Plains, NY ·

Congratulations to Harrison High School Debate Team members Giovanni Cutri '21 and Rebecca Anderson '21 on winning the 2018 Annual Princeton/Yale Debate this weekend!

The event, held at at the German International School in White Plains and hosted by the Yale University and Princeton University Westchester Alumni Clubs, featured debaters from both Yale and Princeton who led a model debate round prior to the high school students' round.

Rebecca and Giovanni affirmed the topic, "Resolved: the electoral college should be abolished." They debated a team from Blind Brook High School, and were assisted by the team from Yale.

After a spirited round, Rebecca and Giovanni were declared the winners, and received a cash prize for their victory.

We look forward to seeing both debaters continue to rack up wins this season!

(Left: Giovanni Cutri '21; right: Rebecca Anderson '21)
